Business Brief -- Amsco International Inc.:
   Company Agrees to Acquire
   Closely Held Finnish Firm
Amsco, based in Pittsburgh, said it plans to operate
Finn-Aqua as part of its Amsco Scientific division, which
makes industrial and laboratory sterilizers, laboratory
glassware, animal care washing equipment and other related
products. The acquisition is scheduled for completion March
1.
   Finn-Aqua, with estimated 1991 sales of $30 million, has
facilities in Hyryla and Hurth, Germany.
   Amsco is a provider of infection control, decontamination
and surgical products and services to the health-care,
scientific and industrial sectors.